<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,258,1591]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1420,1445]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Thai “มดขนปก, 
<emphasis box="[623,780,1420,1445]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">modkhongpok</emphasis>
” or “มดขน, modkhong” for short, the local common name for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[190,311,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mutillidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,258,1591]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1494,1519]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, C." box="[359,521,1494,1519]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="135 - 224" refId="ref58098" refString="Chen, C. - w. (1957) A revision of the velvet ants or Mutillidae of China (Hymenoptera). Quarterly Journal of the Taiwan Museum, 10 (3 - 4), 135 - 224, 6 pls." type="book chapter" year="1957">Chen’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key, this species terminates at couplet 7 of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1870" box="[1082,1237,1495,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Smicromyrme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1082,1237,1495,1518]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Smicromyrme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
key, because the pygidium is smooth and the S1 carina is entire. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel, C. E." box="[741,922,1531,1556]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="177 - 307" refId="ref59784" refString="Mickel, C. E. (1935) The mutillid wasps of the islands of the Pacific Ocean (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 83 (2), 177 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1935. tb 01207. x" type="journal article" year="1935">Mickel’s (1935)</bibRefCitation>
key, it keys to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mickel, 1935)" authorityName="Mickel" authorityYear="1935" baseAuthorityName="Mickel" baseAuthorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Petersenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psecas">
<emphasis box="[1105,1331,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Petersenidia psecas</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel, C. E." pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="177 - 307" refId="ref59784" refString="Mickel, C. E. (1935) The mutillid wasps of the islands of the Pacific Ocean (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 83 (2), 177 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1935. tb 01207. x" type="journal article" year="1935">Mickel, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which is known only from Borneo.
</paragraph>
